<span id="freeTextContainer7124884915362772649">This is an absolutely superb and detailed account of the second day of the battle of Gettysburg.<br/>I read it before going to the battlefield, I read parts of it on the battlefield and I have read it since.<br/>Pfanz is a master of capturing the battle through the eyes of the soldiers who fought there, without ever losing sight of the overall tactical and strategic picture.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


